{{Infobox album | name = Breed 77 | type = studio | artist = [[Breed 77]] | cover = self-titled.jpg | alt = | released = {{flagicon|UK}} December 1, 2000<ref name=amg /> (re-released 2005) | recorded = 2000 | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Alternative metal]], [[flamenco music]] | length = 53:41 | label = [[Infernal Records]] | producer = [[Paul Hoare]] | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = [[Cultura (Breed 77 album)|Cultura]] | next_year = 2004 | misc = {{Extra album cover| | header = Crucifix digi-pak (unfolded) | type = studio | cover = Self-titled crucifix.gif | border = | alt = | caption = }} }}
'''''Breed 77''''' is the debut studio album by [[Gibraltarian people|Gibraltarian]] [[Flamenco music|flamenco]] [[Metal music|metal]] band [[Breed 77]]. It was originally released in 2000 and re-released in 2005 due to popular demand.<ref name=amg>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r830103|pure_url=yes}} Breed 77], [[Allmusic]]. Accessed on line December 24, 2007.</ref> The album was also released as a limited edition in a crucifix-style fold-out digipak. In 2005 "''Shadows''" from this album was released as a single.
All tracks in this album written by Breed 77 and produced, mixed and engineered by Paul Hoare.
