'''Campiña Sur''' ({{lang-ext|Campiña Sul}}) is an administrative division ([[comarca]]) in the [[Badajoz (province)|province of Badajoz]], [[Extremadura]], [[Spain]]. Its capital and administrative center is the [[municipality]] of [[Llerena, Badajoz|Llerena]]. It contains 21 municipalities and 32,841 inhabitants in an area of {{convert|2,798|sqkm|sqmi}}.
The comarca is located in the southeast of the province. To the north, it borders the comarcas of [[La Serena, Spain|La Serena]], [[Tierra de Mérida - Vegas Bajas]] and [[Tierra de Barros]]; to the west, it borders [[Sierra Suroeste]]; and to the southwest, it borders [[Tentudía]]. Campiña Sur abuts the [[Córdoba (Spanish province)|province of Córdoba]] to the east, and the [[Seville (province)|province of Sevilla]] to the south. == Municipalities == The comarca contains the following municipalities:<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.dip-badajoz.es/municipios/municipio_dinamico/comarca/index_comarca.php?comarca=1|title=Comarca de Campiña Sur|last=|first=|date=|website=Diputación de Badajoz|language=es|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=November 3, 2017}}</ref> {{Div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Ahillones]] * [[Azuaga]] * [[Berlanga, Badajoz|Berlanga]] * [[Campillo de Llerena]] * [[Casas de Reina]] * [[Fuente del Arco]] * [[Granja de Torrehermosa]] * [[Higuera de Llerena]] * [[Llera, Badajoz|Llera]] * [[Llerena, Badajoz|Llerena]] * [[Maguilla]] * [[Malcocinado]] * [[Peraleda del Zaucejo]] * [[Puebla del Maestre]] * [[Reina, Badajoz|Reina]] * [[Retamal de Llerena]] * [[Trasierra]] * [[Usagre]] * [[Valencia de las Torres]] * [[Valverde de Llerena]] * [[Villagarcía de la Torre]] {{div col end}} ==References== {{reflist}} {{Comarcas of Extremadura}}
