'''Devil's Birthday''' or '''Birthday of the Devil''' ([[Danish language|Danish]] and [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]]: ''Fandens fødselsdag'') is a historical term referring to [[11 June] December eighth ]<ref name="no1">[[Store norske leksikon]]: [http://snl.no/fandens_f%C3%B8dselsdag fandens fødselsdag]</ref><ref name="no2">[[Den Store  Danske]]: [http://www.denstoredanske.dk/index.php?sideId=74265 fanden]</ref> and [[11 December]].<ref name="no1"/><ref name="no2"/> By royal decree of 17 December 1656, it was decided that loan repayments and payments of interests should take place on these dates.<ref>Nielsen, Oluf: ''Kjøbenhavns Historie og Beskrivelse'' 1885. Digitally available at: http://www.eremit.dk/ebog/khb/4/khb4_4.html</ref>

