{{Infobox coat of arms |color = #DE2929 |name = Emblem of the Transcaucasian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic |image = Emblem of the Transcaucasian SFSR (1930-1936).svg |image_width = 200px |middle = |middle_width = |middle_caption = |lesser = |lesser_width = |lesser_caption = |armiger = {{Flagicon image|Flag of Transcaucasian SFSR.svg|size=22px}} [[Transcaucasian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic]] |year_adopted = 1923 |year_relinquished= 1936 |crest = |torse = |shield = [[Baroque]] shield with [[hammer and sickle]] |supporters = |compartment = |motto = |orders = |other_elements = [[Red star]], [[sunrise|rising sun]], [[Caucasus mountains]] backdrop, [[factory]], [[oil]] [[drilling rig]]s, [[wheat]], [[cotton]], [[maize]], [[rice]], [[grapes]] |earlier_versions = [[File:Emblem of the Transcaucasian SFSR (1924-1930).svg|80px]] [[File:Emblem of the Transcaucasian SFSR (1923-1924).svg|80px]] [[File:Emblem of the Transcaucasian SFSR (1922-1924).svg|80px]] |use = }} {{unreferenced|date=September 2018}} The '''Emblem of the Transcaucasian SFSR''' was adopted by the government of the [[Transcaucasian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic|Transcaucasian SFSR]]. The final version was adopted in 1930.
The emblem is based loosely on the [[State Emblem of the Soviet Union|state emblem]] of the [[Soviet Union]]. It incorporates designs from each of the three major groups that combined in the Transcaucasian SFSR, the [[Armenians]], [[Azeri]] and [[Georgian people|Georgians]], and unusually features [[Islam]]ic art and [[communist]] elements side by side. The [[latticework]] in the star itself bespeaks the former [[Coat of arms of Georgia (country)|coat of arms of Georgia]] from 1918-1921 and adopted again from 1991-2004; the [[crescent]] represents the Muslim Azeris, on a background depicting the national symbol of the Armenians, [[Mount Ararat]]. The rising sun stands for the future, the star as well as the [[hammer and sickle]] for the victory of [[communism]] and the "world-wide socialist community of states".
In 1936, the republic was dissolved and the three regions became the [[Georgian Soviet Socialist Republic|Georgian]], [[Armenian Soviet Socialist Republic|Armenian]], and [[Azerbaijan Soviet Socialist Republic|Azerbaijan SSR]] respectively.
==See also== * [[Emblem of the Armenian Soviet Socialist Republic|Emblem of the Armenian SSR]] * [[Emblem of the Azerbaijan Soviet Socialist Republic|Emblem of the Azerbaijan SSR]] * [[Emblem of the Georgian Soviet Socialist Republic|Emblem of the Georgian SSR]] * [[Flag of the Transcaucasian Socialist Federative Soviet Republic|Flag of the Transcaucasian SFSR]] {{Caucasus-stub}} {{Heraldry-stub}}
