'''Francisco Fernández de la Cueva y Girón, 4th Duke of Alburquerque''' (in full, {{lang-es|[[Don (honorific)|Don]] Francisco Fernández de la Cueva y Téllez-Girón, cuarto duque de Alburquerque, cuarto conde de Ledesma, cuarto conde de Huelma, primer marqués de Cuéllar, señor de los estados de Mombeltrán y Pedro Bernardo}}) (c. 1510&ndash;1563) was a [[Spain|Spanish]] nobleman.

He was the son of Don [[Beltrán de la Cueva, 3rd Duke of Alburquerque]] and of Doña Isabel Girón. He fought in Africa and participated in the siege at [[La Goletta]] and the [[Conquest of Tunis (1535)|Conquest of Tunis]] in 1535.

He married Doña Constanza de Leiva, daughter of the principe di Ascoli, and later (1549) Doña María Fernández de la Córdoba, daughter of Luis Fernández de Córdoba, 2nd Marquis of Comares.

