[[File:International Federation for Research in Women's History logo.gif|thumb|right]] The '''International Federation for Research in Women's History''' ('''IFRWH''') is an international organisation whose aim is "to encourage and coordinate research in all aspects of women's history at international level...". It was founded in 1987.<ref name=about>{{cite web|title=About the Federation|url=http://www.ifrwh.com/about-the-federation|publisher=IFRWH|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref> <ref name=whn>{{cite web|title=International Federation for Research in Women's History|url=https://womenshistorynetwork.org/international-federation-for-research-in-womens-history-ifrwh/|publisher=Women's History Network|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref><ref name="uia">{{cite web|title=International Federation for Research in Women's History (IFRWH)|url=https://www.uia.org/s/or/en/1100032275|website=Union of International Associations|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref> It is also known as the '''Fédération Internationale Pour la Recherche en Histoire des Femmes''' ('''FIRHF''') and the '''International Federation for Promotion of Research into Women's and Gender History'''.<ref name=home />
It organises or jointly organises international conferences: that in 2018 is to be held at [[Simon Fraser University]] in [[Vancouver]], [[Canada]], on the theme "Transnationalisms, Transgressions, Translations".<ref name="conf2018">{{cite web|title=Welcome to the 2018 IFRWH Conference|url=http://www.femst.ucsb.edu/ifrwh/|website=Department of Feminist Studies|publisher=UC Santa Barbara|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref><ref name="home">{{cite web|title=Home page|url=http://www.ifrwh.com/|publisher=IFRWH|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref> The 2000 conference was held in [[Oslo]] with the theme "Conflict and Co-Operation in Sites of Cultural Co-Existence: Perspectives from Women's History".<ref name="conf2000">{{cite web|last1=Offen|first1=Karen|title=The International Federation for Research in Women's History: The Oslo Meeting|url=https://www.historians.org/publications-and-directories/perspectives-on-history/november-2000/the-international-federation-for-research-in-womens-history-the-oslo-meeting|accessdate=1 June 2017|date=2000}}</ref>
Membership is mainly through national committees of researchers, such as the UK Women's History Network.<ref name=whn /> or the Bangladesh National Committee.<ref name="bangla">{{cite web|title=Bangladesh National Committee|url=http://www.ifrwh.com/bangladesh|publisher=IFRWH|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>
The Federation is an Affiliated International Organisation of the [[International Committee of Historical Sciences]].<ref name=about /><ref>{{cite web|title=International Federation for Research in Women’s History|url=http://www.cish.org/index.php/en/members/international-organisations/international-federation-for-research-in-womens-history/|publisher=International Committee of Historical Sciences|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>
The Federation was founded in 1987 and held its initial conference in 1989 at the [[Rockefeller_Foundation#Bellagio_Center|Rockefeller Foundation's Bellagio Center]]. Many of the papers presented there were published as ''Writing Women's History'' (1991, Springer: {{ISBN|9781349215126}}).<ref name="writing">{{cite book|last1=Offen|first1=Karen M|last2=Piersen|first2=Ruth Roach|last3=Rendall|first3=Jane|title=Writing Women’s History: International Perspectives|date=1991|publisher=Springer|isbn=9781349215126|page=xix|url=https://books.google.com.mx/books?id=7vOuCwAAQBAJ&lpg=PR15&dq=International%20Federation%20for%20Research%20in%20Women's%20History&pg=PR19#v=onepage&q=International%20Federation%20for%20Research%20in%20Women's%20History&f=false}}</ref> The inaugural president was [[Ida Blom]], who is {{as of|lc=yes|June 2017}} an honorary board member.<ref name=about /><ref>{{cite web|title=International Federation for Research in Women's History (IFRWH) Conference|url=http://www.ifrwh-bulgaria2007.org/|website=ifrwh-bulgaria|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>
