easure'']] |23 June 2000 |A [[bulk carrier|bulk ore carrier]] that developed a hole in its hull and sank under tow northwest of [[Cape Town]], causing an oil spill that killed around 2,000 endangered [[African penguin]]s. |{{coord|33|40.30|S|18|19.90|E|name=MV Treasure oil spill}} |- |[[SS Wafra oil spill|SS ''Wafra'']] |28 February 1971 |An oil tanker that grounded near [[Cape Agulhas]], causing an oil spill. The ship was later refloated, towed out to sea, and re-sunk to avoid further contamination of the coastline. |{{coord|36|57|S|20|42|E|name=SS Wafra}} |- | {{ship||Waterloo|1815 ship|2}} |28 August 1842 |A British [[convict ship]] that was driven ashore in [[Table Bay]] by a storm, together with the troop transport ''Abercrombie Robinson''. | |}
