{{Expand Italian|Diocesi di Kiyinda-Mityana|date=February 2011}} {{Infobox diocese |image = File:Uganda-2015 123.JPG |caption = St. Noa Mawaggali Cathedral |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Kiyinda–Mityana |latin = Dioecesis Kiyindaensis-Mityanaensis |country = {{flag|Uganda}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kampala|Kampala]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 11,965 |population = 829,488 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 337,963 |catholics_percent= 40.7 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Joseph Anthony Zziwa]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Kiyinda–Mityana''' ({{lang-la|Kiyindaën(sis) – Mityanaën(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the cities of [[Kiyinda]] and [[Mityana]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kampala|Kampala]] in [[Uganda]].
==History== * July 17, 1981: Established as Diocese of Kiyinda–Mityana from Metropolitan Archdiocese of Kampala ===Construction of Cathedral=== [[File:Exhibition in Vatican City, 1960s.jpg|thumb|left|Display of plans of the proposed cathedral, Vatican City]] The cathedral of St. Noa Mawaggali was constructed between 1963-5. <gallery> File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 1.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 2.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 3.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 4.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 5.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 6.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 7.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 8.jpg File:St Noa Mawaggali construction 9.jpg </gallery>
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Kiyinda–Mityana (Roman rite) ** Bishop Joseph Anthony Zziwa (since 2004.10.23)<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bzziwa.html Bishop Joseph Anthony Zziwa Ordained Bishop on March 16, 2002. Appointed Bishop of Kiyinda-Mityana on October 23, 2004]</ref> ** Bishop [[Joseph Mukwaya]] (1988.06.21 – 2004.10.23) ** [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] [[Emmanuel Wamala]] (1981.07.17 – 1988.06.21)
