The '''Young Men's Muslim Association''' ({{lang-ar|جمعية الشبان المسلمين}}) (''Jam'iyyat al-Shubban al-Muslimin'') was founded in [[Egypt]] in 1926, two years before the founding of the [[Muslim Brotherhood]]. By the end of the decade it had around 15,000 members. The leader of the YMMA in [[Palestine (region)|Palestine]] was [[Izz ad-Din al-Qassam|Izz al-din Qassam]].<ref>[[Conor Cruise O'Brian|O'Brien, Conor Cruise]] (1986) ''The Siege. The Story of Israel and Zionism.'' 1988 Paladin Edition. {{ISBN|0-586-08645-5}}. p.209</ref> [[File:YMMA.jpg|thumb|right|YMMA, [[Acre, Israel|Acre]], 1928]]
